  "notes": "Pernambucano (Recife). Northeastern type. Two strongest north/south isoglosses: (1) NO /t,d/ palatalisation вҖ” tia -> [ЛҲtiЙҗ], leite -> [ЛҲlejtЙӘ] (ALiB: ~10% palatalisation in Recife); (2) open pretonic vowels /e/ -> [Йӣ], /o/ -> [Й”] (menino -> [mЙӣЛҲninКҠ], boneca -> [bЙ”ЛҲnЙӣkЙҗ]). Coda /S/ palatalised to [Кғ,К’] (Recife chiado). Strong dorsal onset /r/; coda /R/ -> aspiration.",
